# Product Requirements Document

Replace this template with your project's PRD before running
`cc-autopipe start`. Aim for ~2KB — the orchestrator only forwards
the first 2048 bytes to each session per SPEC.md §6.1.

## Goal

What is being built, in one paragraph. The why matters more than the
what — Claude infers the what from your acceptance criteria.

## Acceptance criteria

Concrete, testable items. Every cycle's verify.sh decides whether the
project is DONE by checking these.

- [ ] Criterion 1
- [ ] Criterion 2
- [ ] Criterion 3

## Out of scope

Pin down boundaries so Claude doesn't drift.

- Not building X
- Not migrating from Y
- Not handling Z

## Notes

Hand off context that doesn't fit in `context.md`: stakeholder names,
related projects, why a constraint exists. Optional.
